# =============================================================================
# .clinerules - Use Case Specifications
# Business Use Case Documentation Standards
# =============================================================================
# This directory contains specifications for specific business use cases
# that leverage the enterprise AI platform.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DIRECTORY OVERVIEW
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Purpose

This directory groups specifications for business use cases:
- **Arabic AP Invoice Processing** - Arabic language accounts payable automation
- **Trial Balance Review** - Financial close process automation

## Subdirectories

| Directory | Description | Schema | Implementation |
|-----------|-------------|--------|----------------|
| `arabic/` | Arabic AP Invoice HITL specification | docs/schema/arabic/ | src/intelligence/ocr/ |
| `tb/` | Trial Balance Review specification | docs/schema/tb/ | src/intelligence/analytics/ |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# USE CASE SPEC STRUCTURE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Each use case specification MUST follow this standard chapter structure:

1. **Chapter 00: Front Matter**
   - Title, version, document control
   - Executive summary
   - Intended audience

2. **Chapter 01-02: Context & Scope**
   - Business context and problem statement
   - Scope boundaries (in/out)
   - Integration points

3. **Chapter 03-05: Business Requirements**
   - Source document traceability
   - MoSCoW-prioritized requirements
   - Acceptance criteria

4. **Chapter 06-08: Process Design**
   - Workflow state machine
   - HITL interaction patterns
   - Decision points and escalation

5. **Chapter 09-11: Data Model**
   - Entity definitions
   - Schema references
   - Data flow diagrams

6. **Chapter 12-14: AI/ML Integration**
   - Model requirements
   - Quality thresholds
   - Fallback behaviors

7. **Chapter 15-16: Operations**
   - Monitoring and alerting
   - Error handling
   - Audit trail requirements

8. **Appendices**
   - Implementation gaps
   - Future roadmap
   - Reference materials

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPEC-DRIFT SYNCHRONIZATION
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Related Artifacts

When modifying use case specs, ensure synchronization with:

| Artifact Type | Location | Sync Rule |
|---------------|----------|-----------|
| JSON Schemas | docs/schema/<usecase>/ | Data model changes |
| Shared Enums | docs/schema/common/enums.yaml | Enum modifications |
| Implementation | src/intelligence/ | Behavior changes |
| Test Fixtures | tests/fixtures/<usecase>/ | Sample data changes |

## Pre-Change Checklist

Before modifying any use case specification:

- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=<usecase>`
- [ ] Identify all related schemas in spec-code-mapping.yaml
- [ ] Check for shared enum dependencies
- [ ] Verify workflow state machine impact

## Post-Change Checklist

After modifying any use case specification:

- [ ] Update related schemas (if data model changed)
- [ ] Update CHANGELOG in spec directory
- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift` to verify no drift
- [ ] Update spec-code-mapping.yaml if new artifacts added

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NAMING CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## File Naming

| Type | Pattern | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| Main spec | `<usecase>-spec.tex` | `arabic-ap-spec.tex` |
| Chapters | `chapters/XX-name.tex` | `chapters/05-business-req.tex` |
| Fragments | `fragment-*.tex` | `fragment-glossary.tex` |
| References | `references.bib` | `references.bib` |

## Requirement ID Conventions

| Use Case | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Arabic AP | ARA-REQ | ARA-REQ-001 |
| Trial Balance | TB-REQ | TB-REQ-ES01 |
| TB HITL | TB-HITL | TB-HITL-001 |

